The paper proposes a deep-learning based approach for generating high-resolution RGB-D images with completed information from consumer-level RGB-D cameras. This involves the use of new operators for adaptive convolution in a deep-learning network consisting of three cascaded modules. The paper focuses on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) techniques for image completion and super-resolution. Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence (AI) for the deep-learning network. The paper also involves graphics (GR) techniques for generating high-resolution images. Finally, the paper involves multimedia (MM) techniques for processing RGB-D images.
